s used in the way.</p><p><br/></p>','C.D.Cafe，one of member of China Startup Incubator Alliance.','Resources/uploads/f3ccdd27d2000e3f9255a7e3e2c48800.jpg','admin',NULL,1,0,1392703202,1392704096,0),(269,'Himeiji黑猫咖啡馆','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392704297913035.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>Himeiji黑猫咖啡馆</p><p>猫咪咖啡馆已经不足为奇了，在日本Himeiji 出现了一个专门的黑猫咖啡馆。这个咖啡杯叫做Cafe Cafe Nekobiyaka Kuro Neko cm 是猫咪的天堂，这个咖啡馆上个月才开设，里面有10只黑色喵星人。Nekobiyaka 主人表示这可能是日本第一家以黑猫为主题的咖啡馆。</p><p>黑猫咖啡馆按照小时收费，每小时1000日元，可增加半小时500日元。里面的软饮料消费400日元，酒精饮料一般600日元一瓶。</p><p>黑猫咖啡馆有一些规矩，例如顾客不能把猫咪捉起来或者举起来。必须适度的跟猫咪进行互动，不能给他们带来压力。同时小盆友也不许进店玩耍，至少是中学生。</p><p><br/></p><p>Himeiji black cat cafe&nbsp;</p><p>Cat cafe is not surprising in Japan now. In Himeji, there is a special cat cafe opened last month. The coffee cup is called Cafe Nekobiyaka Kuro Neko cm. The cafe is the paradise of cats with 10 black meow star men. Nekobiyaka owner says this may be the first cafe themed with cats in Japan.&nbsp;</p><p>Black Cat cafes are charged by hour, 1,000 yen per hour, with half-hour 500 yen. &nbsp;Soft drink has to consume 400 yen, generally 600 yen for a bottle of alcoholic beverages&nbsp;</p><p>There are some rules of Black Cat cafe, for example, customers can not catch cats or lift them, They have to properly interact with cats without exerting pressure on them. Meanwhile children are not allowed in the cafe, at least middle school students.</p><p><br/></p>','Himeiji black cat cafe ','Resources/uploads/c82dce2bf306e2d293a2ab9751ee5185.jpg','admin',NULL,1,0,1392704311,1392787461,0),(270,'喝咖啡的好处','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392706826891525.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p>喝咖啡的好处</p><p>简介：</p><p>1.咖啡含有一定的营养成分。咖啡的烟碱酸含有维他命B，烘焙后的咖啡豆含量更高。并且有游离脂肪酸、咖啡因、单宁酸等。</p><p>　　2.咖啡对皮肤有益处。咖啡可以促进代谢机能，活络消化器官，对便秘有很大功效。使用咖啡粉洗澡是一种温热疗法，有减肥的作用。</p><p>　　3.咖啡有解酒的功能。酒后喝咖啡，将使由酒精转变而来的乙醛快速氧化，分解成水和二氧化碳而排出体外。</p><p>　　4.咖啡可以消除疲劳。要消除疲劳，必须补充营养、休息与睡眠、促进代谢功能，而咖啡则具有这些功能。</p><p>　　5.一日三杯咖啡可预防胆结石。对于含咖啡因的咖啡，能刺激胆囊收缩，并减少胆汁内容易形成胆结石的胆固醇，最新美国哈佛大学研究人员发现，每天喝两到三杯咖啡的男性，得胆结石的机率低于40%。</p><p>　　6.常喝咖啡可防止放射线伤害。放射线伤害尤其是电器的辐射已成为目前较突出的一种污染。印度笆巴原子研究人员在老鼠实验中得到这一结论，并表示可以应用到人类。</p><p>　　7.咖啡的保健医疗功能。咖啡具有抗氧化及护心、强筋骨、利腰膝、开胃促食、消脂消积、利窍除湿、活血化淤、息风止痉等作用。</p><p>　　8.咖啡对情绪的影响力。实验表明，一般人一天吸收300毫克（约3杯煮泡咖啡）的咖啡因，对一个人的机警和情绪会带来良好的影响。</p><p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392706843139361.jpg\" title=\"卡布奇诺.jpg\"/></p><p>The benefits of drinking coffee&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>Brief introduction:&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>1. Coffee contains certain nutrients. &nbsp;Nicotinic acid of coffee contains vitamin B and baked beans conations higher. And it has a free fatty acids, caffeine, tannic acid, etc.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>2. Coffee is good for your skin. Coffee can boost the metabolic function, activate digestive organs, and has a great effect for constipation. Using coffee as bath powder is a kind of thermotherapy, which can help reduce weight.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>3. Coffee has the function of dispelling the effects of alcohol. Drinking coffee can make acetaldehyde oxidation converted from alcohol deco posited into water and carbon dioxide out of the body.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>4. Coffee can eliminate fatigue. To eliminate fatigue, people must complement nourishment, take a rest, sleep and promote metabolism, and coffee has these functions.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>5. Three cups of coffee a day can prevent gallstones. For caffeinated coffee can boost gallbladder contraction, and reduce cholesterol that could &nbsp;easily be formed into gallstones. Researchers from Harvard University found that men who have two to three cups of coffee a day is 40% &nbsp;lower to have gallstones than those who not.</p><p><br/></p><p>6. Often drink coffee can prevent radiation damage. Radiation damage, especially electrical radiation, has become a prominent kind of pollution. India atomic researchers get the conclusion in mice experiment that could also be applied to humans.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>7. Health care function of coffee. Coffee has the function of oxidation resistance, protecting heart, strong bones and muscles, promoting appetite immunotherapy and dehumidification, and so on.</p><p>8. Coffee has the influence on mood. Experimental results show that the people absorbing 300 mg caffeine a day (about 3 cups of brewed coffee) would bring good effect on people’s mood and ones’ alert.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>','The benefits of drinking coffee ','Resources/uploads/f3ccdd27d2000e3f9255a7e3e2c48800.jpg','admin',NULL,1,0,1392706882,NULL,NULL),(271,'喝咖啡揭露性格，看看你是哪类人','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392706952589908.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p>喝咖啡揭露性格，看看你是哪类人</p><p><br/></p><p>咖啡，是很多人生活中不可或缺的一部分。但原来，咖啡还可以出卖人的心情、看出人的性格特征。神马？解释不准确？哈哈，认真你就输咯，以下推理仅供参考啦。&nbsp;</p><p>意式特浓咖啡Espresso其实是现在多款咖啡的变种，喜欢喝Espresso的人诚实又有点情绪化，受不了蠢人，还很可能做过烟民。</p><p>朱古力咖啡摩卡Mocha口感软绵绵的，甜甜的易入口，但其实外柔内刚，铁石心肠。</p><p>选拿铁Latte的“很傻很天真”，说不定晚上还得要抱着毛绒公仔才能入睡。</p><p>选择超特浓咖啡Corto是那些“超忙超紧张”、连坐下享受一杯饮品的时间也没有的人。</p><p>Macchiato Chiaro，牛奶比咖啡还多，似乎是属于那些连父母都想你快点长大的“大小孩”们。</p><p>Ristretto，实际、直接、爽快；</p><p>为人实际就是美式咖啡Americano的粉丝咯，不过是少做少错、得过且过而已。</p><p>挑玛奇朵咖啡Macchiato的人就有点矛盾，想和别人不同，但又不想太出众，被人领导又乐在其中。</p><p>整天想着人生久了点什么？那就英国是Schiumato的拥蹙了。</p><p>挑Corretto的就是疯狂喝酒喝到失忆，不想被人知道的那些人了。</p><p>选Lungo恐怕就是去Starbucks装酷耍帅扮专家的人了。</p><p>而挑Cappucino Estivo的人就很爱做梦，经常保持自己心境年轻。</p><p><br/></p><p>Coffee can expose your character and personality. Which kind of people do you belong to?&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>Coffee is an integral part of life of many people. However in fact, coffee can also reflect people&#39;s mood and personality. Believe it or not. The following reasons are only for reference.&nbsp;</p><p>Espresso coffee is actually a variant of many coffee, people who like to drink Espresso are honest, sometimes a little emotional and can not stand the fool. Likely they are smokers too.&nbsp;</p><p>Chocolate Mocha coffee taste soft, sweet with easy entrance. People who like it are in fact kind of iron hand in a velvet glove, even with a heart of stone.&nbsp;</p><p>Those who choose Latte are very naive, probly need to hold plush doll to sleep.&nbsp;</p><p>Those who Select Super Espresso Corto are very busy and often feel nervous,&quot; even have no time to sit down and enjoy a drink.&nbsp;</p><p>Macchiato Chiaro has more milk than coffee; people who like it look like a child. Even parents want you to grow up quickly.&nbsp;</p><p>Ristretto lovers are direct and straightforward.&nbsp;</p><p>Americano fans are honest and realistic, just sometimes would muddle along.</p><p>People who chose Macchiato is a little bit contradictory. They want to be different from others while maintaining a low profile and they enjoy being leaded.&nbsp;</p><p>Always thinking that Life is long are British Schiumato fans.&nbsp;</p><p>People who choose Corretto love drinking, unwilling to be known by others.&nbsp;</p><p>Lungo lovers are probably those cool people who like to drink in Starbucks.&nbsp;</p><p>Those who choose Cappuccino Estivolove love dreaming and always keep a young heart.</p><p><br/></p>','Coffee can expose your character and personality. Which kind of people do you belong to? ','Resources/uploads/f3ccdd27d2000e3f9255a7e3e2c48800.jpg','admin',NULL,1,0,1392706979,NULL,NULL),(272,'黑莓Blackberry主题咖啡馆','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707043968218.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>黑莓Blackberry主题咖啡馆</p><p>简介：</p><p>这家咖啡厅名为空中花园咖啡厅（SkyPark Cafe），是RIM与印度本土黑莓网站BBin合作的产物。在这里，客人可以使用咖啡厅提供的PlayBook来上网，或是直接控制点唱机来播放歌曲。同时，PlayBook也兼做菜单之用，顾客可以直接使用它们来进行点单。</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 这家咖啡厅的墙壁内衬有NFC贴纸，方便那些手持具有NFC功能设备的用户获得咖啡厅提供的一些每月推荐应用等等。不知道黑莓粉丝们会不会对这家咖啡厅感兴趣呢？</p><p></p><p>Blackberry theme cafe&nbsp;</p><p>Introduction:&nbsp;</p><p>This cafe is called SkyPark Café, which is the product of the cooperation of RIM and BBin, a local India website Blackberry. Here, customers can use Playbook to connect to the internet or directly control the jukebox to play songs. Meanwhile, Playbook can also be used as the menu to order.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Walls inside the cafe are lined with NFC stickers to recommend Application for customers who have access to NFC-enabled devices. Blackberry fans are you interested in this café?</p><p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707085477071.jpg\" title=\"7_2908717_19e94f683475ec4.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p>','Blackberry theme cafe ','','admin',NULL,1,0,1392707090,NULL,NULL),(273,'咖啡产地的认识','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707256299611.jpg\" title=\"11.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>咖啡产地的认识</p><p>简介：</p><p>东部非洲的埃塞俄比亚（Ethiopia）是咖啡的原产地，关于咖啡发现于埃塞，有个历史故事。</p><p>古代埃塞俄比亚西南部季马地区的名叫卡法（kaffa）的山区，生长着一种结小红果的野生灌木。一位牧羊人发现他的山羊群吃了这种灌木果子后不停地欢闹。于是，他也好奇地摘下一些放在嘴里咀嚼，不多时便备感精神兴奋，因为嚼得过多，他进入醉迷状态。消息传到附近的一座东正教修道院内，一群修道士怀着好奇之心试嚼之后，也产生同样的效力。于是四方的修道士纷纷前来采摘咀嚼这具有非凡“魔力”的小红果，兴奋得长时间不能入睡，以致影响了他们正常的宗教活动。于是教会视这种小红果为“魔鬼豆”，下令禁止其教徒食用。因此，在咖啡被发现后的一个相当长时间内，埃塞俄比亚人是不食用咖啡的，也不懂得制作咖啡茶。</p><p><br/></p><p>在当初发现咖啡时，这种野生的灌木植物还没有名字。当地人就以其生长地“卡法”命其名。以后广传世界的“咖啡”之名就是从“卡法”演变出来的。</p><p><br/></p><p>大约于15世纪左右，咖啡从埃塞俄比亚传到国外。从埃塞北方古都贡德尔的大集市，商人们用骆驼队载着咖啡豆往西北运到苏丹，传入埃及和地中海沿岸国家；往东穿过红海，传到也门和阿拉伯半岛。中东各国人民称之为“阿拉伯咖啡”从那时起，被广泛饮用。后来，又传到远东，最后跨越太平洋传到美洲大陆。现在，巴西成为新的最大的咖啡产地。美国还有一个最大的埃塞俄比亚阿拉伯咖啡市场。</p><p><br/></p><p>Producing area of coffee</p><p>Ethiopia, located in eastern Africa, is the origin of coffee. There is a historical story about the discovery of coffee in Ethiopia. According to the legend, a goat herder from the Kaffa region of southwestern Ethiopia noticed that his goats were more animated and lively after eating some wild red berries. Kaldi then ate some of the berries himself, and sure enough he also felt increased energy. &nbsp;Soon these unique properties of coffee became known to some monks at a nearby monastery, and they too began consuming the beans that helped them meditate and pray for longer periods of time. Other monasteries also began using the berries and could not fall into sleep for a long time so that affected their normal religious activities. Therefore the church treats this small red fruits as devil beans and banned the consumption. Therefore, after a fairly long period of the founding of the coffee, Ethiopians did not eat coffee as well as making coffee tea.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>When coffee was first found, this wild shrub plant has not been named. The locals named it by its living areas. Therefore, the world wide known name “coffee” was revolved from kaffa.</p><p><br/></p><p>Around 15th century, coffee were spread from Ethiopia to abroad. From the grand bazaar of northern Ethiopia&#39;s Gondar, the merchants used camels to carry coffee beans from northwest to Sudan, introduced it into Egypt and Mediterranean countries; east to Yemen and the Arabian Peninsula through the red sea. Middle East people call it Arab coffee. Since then, coffee was widely used and drunk. Later again it was spread to the Far East, finally crossed the Pacific to the Americas. Now the new Brazil has become the largest coffee producer. America has one of the biggest Ethiopia Arabia coffee markets.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p>','Producing area of coffee','','admin',NULL,1,0,1392707281,NULL,NULL),(274,'咖啡与心情','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707332978626.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>咖啡与心情</p><p>你是心情好还是心情不好的时候想喝杯咖啡呢？每个人的答案都不一样，但因为咖啡是心情好的时候喝的饮料，所以唯有在情绪不错时，想看看蓝蓝的天与晒晒温柔的阳光时才能品尝出咖啡的香醇美味。心情不好时你应该去酒吧喝酒解闷。咖啡馆里慵懒的爵士、扣人心弦的歌剧、浪漫的法国香颂或轻柔的钢琴演奏是你最常会听到的音乐。当然这和咖啡馆老板的品位有关。你可以和亲密的朋友或三五知己在一起聊聊天，探讨一下各自感兴趣的话题，随着时间的深入，你会发现心情渐渐的平静，甚至有一些感动，所有的理由都很单纯、随兴。当你感觉今天心情不错时来一杯咖啡吧，你会发现咖啡最美好的一面。</p><p><br/></p><p>Coffee and Mood&nbsp;</p><p>When do you prefer to have a cup of coffee, in good mood or bad mood? Every person has a different answer. However, coffee should be tasted in a good mood. &nbsp;So only when you have the mood to look at the blue sky and enjoy the gentle sunshine can you taste the fragrance of the coffee。You should go to the pub when you are in a bad mood. Lazy jazz, heart-thrilling opera, romantic French chansons or gentle piano would often be played in cafes. Of course it is related to the grade of the owner. You can chat with your friends, discuss topics of common interest. With the deepening of time, you will find yourself gradually become calm and even feel moved, while all reasons are quite simple. &nbsp;Have a cup of coffee when you are in the good mood, you will find the best of coffee.</p><p><br/></p><p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707356221933.jpg\" title=\"0.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p>','Coffee and Mood ','','admin',NULL,1,0,1392707384,NULL,NULL),(275,'卖萌hold不住 探秘俄罗斯的女仆咖啡屋','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707437261591.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>卖萌hold不住 探秘俄罗斯的女仆咖啡屋</p><p>简介：</p><p>女仆这东西是西方的产物，在中国女仆应该称为丫鬟，而女仆到了日本被萌化后就成了一种日本文化再次得以传播，女仆咖啡屋也变得流行起来，我国魔都就有很多女仆咖啡屋，而现在在俄罗斯也有了模仿日本萌系女仆咖啡屋的。不过俄罗斯的软妹子穿起女仆装更萌更好看一点，毕竟有金发碧眼的靓妹。这就让我想起了在女子网球界的“俄罗斯粉红军团”，库尔尼科娃啦、莎拉波娃啦等。不过对于很多俄罗斯好看的妹子来说，就是长大了容易走形变样。</p><p><br/></p><p>Acting Cute. Maid cafe in Russia &nbsp;</p><p>Brief introduction:&nbsp;</p><p>Maid is the product of the west, and they were called servant girls in china. However now it has become a Japanese culture to spread again. Maid cafe also became popular then. China’s magic city Shanghai also has a lot of maid café. And now in Russia there is a copy of maid café too. But waitress in Russia&#39;s would looks more cute in maid outfit. ,after all, they are blue-eyed and golden-haired beauties. This reminds me of the &quot;Russian pink legion&quot; in women&#39;s tennis, kournikova, Maria sharapova, etc. But for many Russian girls, it is hard to keep figure when they grow up.</p><p><br/></p><p></p><p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707454539939.jpg\" style=\"float:none;\" title=\"0 (5).jpg\"/></p><p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707455109040.jpg\" style=\"float:none;\" title=\"0 (6).jpg\"/></p><p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707475312427.jpg\" title=\"0 (1).jpg\"/></p>','Acting Cute. Maid cafe in Russia ','','admin',NULL,1,0,1392707479,NULL,NULL),(276,'收吻不收钱的咖啡馆','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707527130153.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>收吻不收钱的咖啡馆</p><p>简介：</p><p>位于澳大利亚悉尼的一家法式咖啡馆“地铁圣詹姆斯”（Metro St. James）本月想出了一种独特的浪漫促销方式。只要在当地时间早上9点到11点之间光顾这家咖啡馆，情侣之间给对方一个吻，就可以不用支付咖啡的价钱。</p><p><br/></p><p>No money only kisses.</p><p>Introduction:&nbsp;</p><p>Metro St James, a French cafe located in Sydney, Australia, has come up with a unique romantic promotion this month : from 9:00 to 11:00 in the morning ,couples do not have to pay for the coffee as long as they give each other a kiss .</p><p><br/></p>','No money only kisses.','','admin',NULL,1,0,1392707533,NULL,NULL),(277,'维也纳咖啡馆文化入非遗','<p><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707603102144.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p>维也纳咖啡馆文化入非遗</p><p>简介：</p><p>有句话说“我不在咖啡馆，就在去咖啡馆的路上”，用这句话形容奥地利维也纳人再合适不过，在咖啡馆里看报聊天早就成为当地人的一种生活方式。近日，联合国教科文组织正式将维也纳咖啡馆以及咖啡馆文化列入“非物质文化遗产”。下面就让我们跟随镜头去体验地道的“咖啡生活方式”。&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp; 维也纳、威尼斯、巴黎并称为欧洲三大咖啡名城，三个城市的咖啡引进和制作技法全部传自古老国家土耳其，其中又以维也纳最先，早在16世纪中叶维也纳人就掌握了咖啡制作和调制技术。1685年维也纳兴建了第一批咖啡馆，</p><p><br/></p><p>到1900年城里已有超过600家咖啡馆。虽然第一次世界大战给维也纳的咖啡馆造成一定破坏，不过得益于战后恢复和扩建，维也纳的咖啡馆眼下已经是“遍地开花”。都说欧洲咖啡文化底蕴深厚，维也纳人更要举双手赞成，城里的咖啡馆不仅数量多，而且多是百年以上历史的老店，一种“咖啡生活方式”在维也纳低调蔓延。花上几欧元买一杯香浓的咖啡，人们就可以在古老的咖啡馆里坐上几个小时甚至一整天，也不会招致服务生的白眼，于是咖啡馆成了维也纳人读书、看报、写作、聊天等各种活动的场所……把它称为维也纳人第二个家一点也不为过。近日，联合国教科文组织将维也纳咖啡馆及其文化列入“非物质文化遗产”，这一决定意味着维也纳特有的“咖啡生活方式”将得到保护和延续。如果您有机会去维也纳，不妨来一杯热咖啡，在氤氲的香气中悠哉地享受一下“慢生活”吧。</p><p><br/></p><p>Viennese coffee culture listed as UNESCO intangible heritage</p><p>Brief introduction:&nbsp;</p><p>There is a saying &quot;if I&#39;m not in a cafe, I must on the way to a café”, which is fitting and proper to describe people&#39;s life in Vienna. Reading newspapers or chatting in cafes has become a way of life of the locals. Recently, UNESCO has officially listed Vienna&#39;s coffee house culture as an intangible heritage. Let us follow the lens to experience the real coffee life.&nbsp;</p><p><br/></p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Vienna, Venice, Paris are known as the three European coffee cities, all its coffee introduction and production techniques come from the ancient country Turkey. &nbsp;Vienna is the first city to have mastered production and modulation technologies In the middle of the 16th century .and it built the first cafes in 1685.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp;In 1900, the city has more than 600 cafes. Although the First World War has brought Vienna cafes certain damages, due to the post-war recovery and expansion Vienna cafe is now &quot;blossoming &quot;. &nbsp;European coffee culture is deep and profound, which is also true for Vienna. The city has a great number of cafes and most of them have a history of more than one hundred years. Coffee lifestyle is now spreading in Vienna. By buying one cup of coffee people can turn a table into their own private space for hours on end, and no waiter will urge them to order more. People come here to chat with friends, read newspapers, and write and so on. Café is the second home of Viennese. Recently, UNESCO has listed Vienna&#39;s coffee house and its culture as an intangible heritage, which means Vienna’s unique &quot;coffee lifestyle will be protected and extended in time. If you have the chance to go to Vienna, try a cup of hot coffee, and enjoy the &quot;slow life&quot;.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>','Viennese coffee culture listed as UNESCO intangible heritage','','admin',NULL,1,0,1392707607,NULL,NULL),(278,'C.D.Cafe 魅影之夜','<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\"><img src=\"http://cdcafe.cc/Common/libs/ueditor/../../../Resources/uploads//20140218/1392707977117855.jpg\" title=\"2.jpg\"/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">C.D.Cafe&nbsp;魅影之夜</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">你是否希望生活在书本和论文的世界之外还有小说般绮丽的感觉？</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">你是否期待幽蓝暮光的深处有冥冥中注定的缘分？</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\"><br/></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">爱探险，爱音乐，爱神秘。</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\"><br/></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">爱时尚，爱交友，更爱自由。</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\"><br/></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">我是爱德华。</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">我在C.D&nbsp;Cafe等你。</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\"><br/></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">一、活动时间：2013.9.20晚18:30~21:30</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">二、活动地点：C.D&nbsp;Cafe</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">C.D.Cafe&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">“THE&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">MASK&nbsp;NIGHT</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">”</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(43, 43, 43);font-size: 16px;font-family: 微软雅黑;background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250)\">Do&nbsp;